value.0:
*The old man looks up from a stack of papers*

Aye? What c'n I do for ye, stranger?
Yeah?
Ah, all right, then. Open up yer bag an' let's see what ye've got there, <mister/missus>.
Nay, not at the moment. Jus' bring me any o' them bandit helms ye might find.

Comment.value: If the quest hasnt been completed

value.0:
*The old man looks you over as if sizing you up, then nods slowly.*

Well, there's a band o' crazed men who've been givin' folks along th' North Road a lot o' trouble lately. If they aren't taken care o' soon, they might decide t' make a raid on Osthavn itsel'.

If y'r willin' to help out, I'll pay ye 25 coins for each one ye put down. Ye can bring me their helms as proof.
*The Burgomaster nods acknowledgement and gives you a distracted wave of the hand as he returns his attention to his papers.*
Oooh, well... This be the town of Osthavn, as I'm sure ye've noticed, an' I'm th' Burgomaster - the Mayor, if ye will.

Fun? Hah! 

*He cackles, then coughs several times into a filthy handkerchief* 

We do our work, we pay our taxes t' th' Jarl, an' if we've anythin' left, we spend it at th' Tankard, down by th' docks, drinkin'.

Th' town o' Osthavn's part o' the Jarldom of Ostland, one o' four jarldoms on th' island. The Jarl himsel' - we call him th' Axe - lives in the fortress o' Ostdur, north o' here. The only other town o' any size in Ostland is Havskar, on th' northern tip o' th' island. Fisherfolk, they are, an' like strangers even less than we do here - er, no offence t' ye, <mister/missus>.
That'd be Agnar Magnus. Accordin' t' th' Axe, he's a pretender an' in th' pay o' the Luskans.

Well, d'ye see, the Bathries've long been rulers o' Ostland, but durin' the reign o' Wiltun II, Agnar's granddad Pimpant Magnus took over after all the Bathries died off. It, uh, seems folks weren't too happy with the way things were under the Bathries, who were livin' rather th' high life, an' were pleased t' put someone else in charge. 

Th' story's a bit murky, but he let th' Amians an' Luskans in an' sold all our iron an' lumber to them. Seems he might also have killed off a few other nobles along th' way. In any event, he was chased out an' there was a rebellion against Axe Wiltun II in Ottar, who marched right in an' put Pimpant's son Heinrich on the throne. Then durin' th' war with Luskan, Heinrich was killed, but his son Agnar - th' one on th' posters - escaped. A distant relative o' th' original Bathrie line is back on th' throne now, so ye can maybe see how things stand.

Let's just say I work for th' Axe, so I have t' enforce his laws. At th' same time, I might also say that hist'ry tends t' repeat itself, an' th' current Axe could maybe stand t' learn a bit from what happened t' his ancestor, if ye see what I mean?

An' ye better not be repeatin' any o' this around th' Everwatch Knights or ye'll find out just how much th' Jarl doesn' like hearin' that sort o' stuff.

Hmm, well....

*He rubs his chin in thought.*

'Tis said the Northmen - which is what we are, here in Ostland - came up from th' Moonshaes more'n a thousand years ago an' settled Ruathym an' parts o' the Sword Coast an' became traders an' seafarers.  We've fought a couple o' wars with Luskan pirates, but otherwise we pretty much just minds our own business, sellin' lumber an' furs an' such.

Before th' Time o' Troubles, durin' th' last war with Luskan, th' islands o' th' Ruathym region - that's th' big island here, plus Caraigh, Wiltun, Axard an', uh... Nerth... were united under th' First Axe Aumark Lithyl. He ruled from Holgerstead, in th' Jarldom o' Ottar, t' the' south o' here. He was th' second in command t' Verthain Wiltun - that be Wiltun III - an' took over when he got killed.

Aye. That there Lord Wiltun - the fifth o' the name - is the grandson o' Verthain. It gets kind o' complicated, d'ye see...

Th' Axe Wiltun III - Verthain - was Jarl o' Ottar durin' th' war. His son Wiltun IV succeeded him while Aumark became th' First Axe. So Verthain pledged his loyalty t' Aumark on condition he an' his family be allowed to continue rulin' as Jarls o' Wiltun Keep itself, which had always been in their family. So Aumark an' then his son Thorden after him took over in Ottar an' the Wiltuns went off t' their own piece o' rock.

Aye, well, ye'd think so, wouldn' ye? An' now the current Axe Wiltun, Arsant - he bein' the fifth - is buildin' up his own fleet an' has his eyes on Caraigh. Ye figure it out from there.

Not sure our own Jarl is payin' too much attention to that, though...
Th' Axe's personal guard. You'll see them around, I'm sure. Big horns on their helmets an' all that. They enforce his laws. Just as soon cut ye down as look at ye.

Well, d'ye see, the militia only keep order here in town, whereas th' Everwatch Knights're th' Axe's army. They're not very pop'lar in Osthavn, but there isn't much anyone can do without 'going to Ostdur' themselves.

Aye. They show no mercy t' anyone they think might be breaking th' Jarl's law. People who go into the dungeons of Ostdur almost never return. 

*He looks furtively around the room again.*

But ye didn't hear that from me, <mister/missus>.

Raorik Bathrie be his name, th' Axe o' Ostland. We Northmen are normally pretty loose when it comes t' government, but Bathrie keeps a tight grip on things 'round here. 

*He glances around nervously for a moment.*

Jus' make sure ye dont run afoul o' his Everwatch Knights, stranger.
I came about some work.
I'm here to collect on a job.
I'll be going now.
Do you have any other work I could do for you?
I was wondering if you might have some work available?
All right, I'll remember that if I happen to come across any.
Good <day/night> to you, then.
I wonder if you can tell me more about this place.
I see. What do people do for fun around here?
What else can you tell me?
Thanks for your time. Have a good <day/night>.
Who's this Magnus fellow mentioned on the posters outside your door?
'According to the Axe'?
What do you think?
Thanks for your time. Have a good <day/night>.
Can you tell me a bit about the history of Ostland?
What about more recent history?
Wiltun? Any relation to Lord Wiltun of Wiltun Keep?
That seems like a bit of a step down, from ruling the whole of Ottar to just Wiltun Keep?
Thanks for the information. I'll be going now.
What are the Everwatch Knights?
Do you mean literally? The town guard doesn't stop them?
'Going to Ostdur'?
Thanks for the information. I'll be going now.
The Jarl? Who's he?
Thanks for your time. I should be going now.
